{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"AstronomyKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Celestial Positions"},"abstract":[{"text":"Calculate the positions of celestial bodies in various coordinate systems.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/astronomykit\/celestialpositions"]}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AstronomyKit can calculate positions for the Sun, Moon, planets, Jupiter’s moons, and user-defined stars. Positions can be expressed in multiple coordinate systems."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Celestial-Bodies","text":"Celestial Bodies","type":"heading","level":2},{"anchor":"Available-Bodies","text":"Available Bodies","type":"heading","level":3},{"code":["\/\/ Major bodies","let sun = CelestialBody.sun","let moon = CelestialBody.moon","let mars = CelestialBody.mars","","\/\/ All planets (Mercury through Neptune)","for planet in CelestialBody.planets {","    print(planet.name)","}","","\/\/ Jupiter's Galilean moons","for moon in CelestialBody.galileanMoons {","    print(moon.name)  \/\/ Io, Europa, Ganymede, Callisto","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Body-Properties","text":"Body Properties","type":"heading","level":3},{"code":["let mars = CelestialBody.mars","","print(mars.name)           \/\/ \"Mars\"","print(mars.orbitalPeriod)  \/\/ ~686 days","print(mars.massProduct)    \/\/ Mass × G in AU³\/day²","print(mars.isPlanet)       \/\/ true","print(mars.isNakedEyeVisible)  \/\/ true"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Looking-Up-Bodies-by-Name","text":"Looking Up Bodies by Name","type":"heading","level":3},{"code":["if let body = CelestialBody(name: \"Jupiter\") {","    print(\"Found: \\(body)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Horizon-Coordinates","text":"Horizon Coordinates","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Where does a body appear in your local sky?"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let observer = Observer(latitude: 40.7128, longitude: -74.0060)","let mars = try CelestialBody.mars.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","","print(\"Altitude: \\(mars.altitude)°\")     \/\/ Height above horizon","print(\"Azimuth: \\(mars.azimuth)°\")       \/\/ Compass bearing","print(\"Direction: \\(mars.compassDirection)\")  \/\/ N, NE, E, SE, etc.","","if mars.isAboveHorizon {","    print(\"Mars is visible!\")","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Equatorial-Coordinates","level":2,"text":"Equatorial Coordinates","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Right ascension and declination on the celestial sphere:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let eq = try CelestialBody.saturn.equatorial(at: .now)","","print(\"RA: \\(eq.rightAscension) hours\")","print(\"Dec: \\(eq.declination)°\")","print(\"Distance: \\(eq.distance) AU\")","","\/\/ Formatted output","print(eq.rightAscensionFormatted)   \/\/ \"02h 15m 30.2s\"","print(eq.declinationFormatted)      \/\/ \"+12° 34' 56.7\"\""],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Equator-Date-Options","level":3,"text":"Equator Date Options","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Choose the reference equinox:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ J2000 coordinates (default) - standard reference epoch","let j2000 = try body.equatorial(at: .now, equatorDate: .j2000)","","\/\/ Coordinates of the observation date - accounts for precession","let ofDate = try body.equatorial(at: .now, equatorDate: .ofDate)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Ecliptic-Coordinates","level":2,"text":"Ecliptic Coordinates","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Position relative to the ecliptic plane:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let longitude = try CelestialBody.venus.eclipticLongitude(at: .now)","print(\"Venus ecliptic longitude: \\(longitude)°\")","","\/\/ Sun's full ecliptic position","let sunPos = try Sun.position(at: .now)","print(\"Sun: λ=\\(sunPos.longitude)°, β=\\(sunPos.latitude)°\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Position-Vectors","level":2,"text":"Position Vectors","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cartesian coordinates in 3D space:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Geocentric (from Earth's center)","let geo = try CelestialBody.jupiter.geoPosition(at: .now)","print(\"Distance from Earth: \\(geo.magnitude) AU\")","","\/\/ Heliocentric (from Sun's center)","let helio = try CelestialBody.mars.helioPosition(at: .now)","print(\"Distance from Sun: \\(helio.magnitude) AU\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Distance-Calculations","level":2,"text":"Distance Calculations","type":"heading"},{"code":["\/\/ Distance from Sun","let auFromSun = try CelestialBody.mars.distanceFromSun(at: .now)","print(\"Mars is \\(auFromSun) AU from the Sun\")","","\/\/ Angular separation from Sun","let angle = try CelestialBody.venus.angleFromSun(at: .now)","print(\"Venus is \\(angle)° from the Sun\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Constellation-Identification","level":2,"text":"Constellation Identification","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Find which constellation contains a body:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let constellation = try CelestialBody.mars.constellation(at: .now)","print(\"\\(constellation.symbol) - \\(constellation.name)\")","\/\/ Output: \"Tau - Taurus\"","","\/\/ Or from raw coordinates","let orion = try Constellation.find(ra: 5.9195, dec: 7.4071)","print(orion.name)  \/\/ \"Orion\""],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"User-Defined-Stars","level":2,"text":"User-Defined Stars","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Define custom stars for position calculations:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Define Sirius at star slot 1","try CelestialBody.star1.define(","    ra: 6.7525,           \/\/ Right ascension in hours","    dec: -16.7161,        \/\/ Declination in degrees","    distanceLightYears: 8.6",")","","\/\/ Now use it like any other body","let position = try CelestialBody.star1.equatorial(at: .now)","let constellation = try CelestialBody.star1.constellation(at: .now)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Eight star slots are available: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".star1"},{"type":"text","text":" through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".star8"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Aberration-Correction","level":2,"text":"Aberration Correction","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control light-time and aberration corrections:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ With correction (default) - apparent position","let apparent = try body.geoPosition(at: .now, aberration: .corrected)","","\/\/ Without correction - geometric position","let geometric = try body.geoPosition(at: .now, aberration: .none)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Refraction-Correction","level":2,"text":"Refraction Correction","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Atmospheric refraction affects horizon coordinates:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\/\/ Normal refraction (default)","let normal = try body.horizon(at: .now, from: observer, refraction: .normal)","","\/\/ No refraction","let geometric = try body.horizon(at: .now, from: observer, refraction: .none)","","\/\/ JPL Horizons model","let jpl = try body.horizon(at: .now, from: observer, refraction: .jplHorizons)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Position-Calculations","title":"Position Calculations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit